##-> Allows clients on the external network to use LDAP directory services 
##-> from servers on the internal network. These rules are only enabled if
##-> Masquerading is disabled.
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @EXTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 389 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @EXTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 389 -d @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @INTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 389 -d @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @INTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 389 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A forward -i @INTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 -d @INTNET@ 389 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
##NOMASQ: @IPCHAINS@ -A forward -i @EXTDEV@ -s @INTNET@ 389 -d @EXTNET@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
